WEBVTT

00:02.535 --> 00:05.038
[***]

00:06.706 --> 00:10.443
CHRIS ROCK:
<i>1983 was my first</i>
<i>Valentine's Day as a teenager.</i>

00:10.477 --> 00:13.480
<i>I never really cared</i>
<i>about Valentine's Day before,</i>

00:13.513 --> 00:16.316
<i>but now I couldn't ignore it.</i>

00:16.349 --> 00:18.284
<i>Valentine's Day makes</i>
<i>most people</i>

00:18.318 --> 00:20.153
<i>think of flowers and candy,</i>

00:20.186 --> 00:23.690
<i>but it reminded me of the</i>
<i>gangland massacre in Chicago.</i>

00:23.723 --> 00:26.159
Happy Valentine's Day.

00:27.327 --> 00:31.064
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

00:32.766 --> 00:35.301
<i>Yesterday,</i>
<i>those roses cost $10.</i>

00:35.335 --> 00:37.637
<i>Today, they're $110.</i>

00:37.671 --> 00:40.173
<i>Even when you're broke,</i>
<i>you have to find a way</i>

00:40.206 --> 00:42.609
<i>to tell your woman</i>
<i>you love her.</i>

00:42.642 --> 00:44.444
OFFICER:
Hey!

00:45.745 --> 00:47.447
You picked the wrong wall today!

00:47.480 --> 00:50.316
<i>Even if it means getting</i>
<i>the crap beat out of you.</i>

00:50.350 --> 00:53.653
<i>On Valentine's Day,</i>
<i>love was in the air.</i>

00:53.687 --> 00:56.589
<i>You should have seen what</i>
<i>they did after they shot him.</i>

00:58.491 --> 01:02.228
Hey.
Hi. Happy Valentine's Day.

01:02.262 --> 01:05.832
<i>Even at school, Valentine's Day</i>
<i>was a big deal, and it seemed</i>

01:05.865 --> 01:08.435
<i>like everybody was getting</i>
<i>something except me.</i>

01:08.468 --> 01:11.338
Still a few days to go.
We could still get a card.

01:11.371 --> 01:13.340
<i>That look means,</i>
<i>"If we weren't friends,</i>

01:13.373 --> 01:15.375
<i>I'd smack the hope out of you."</i>

01:15.408 --> 01:17.844
Hey, I got one. I got
a Valentine's Day card.

01:17.877 --> 01:19.446
Cool.

01:19.479 --> 01:21.881
Hey, if I got a card,
I know you will.

01:21.915 --> 01:24.117
What's it say?

01:26.786 --> 01:28.588
Roses are red, violets are blue,

01:28.621 --> 01:30.924
you stink like a monkey
and look like one too.

01:30.957 --> 01:33.360
Happy Valentine's Day.
BOY: Loser!

01:33.393 --> 01:35.562
<i>So much for love in the air.</i>

01:35.595 --> 01:38.131
[***]

01:43.336 --> 01:46.172
<i>* Aw, make it funky now </i>

02:10.263 --> 02:11.898
[***]

02:11.931 --> 02:14.567
<i>I didn't have any luck</i>
<i>with girls when I was 13.</i>

02:14.601 --> 02:17.604
<i>Mostly, I just had</i>
<i>a bunch of crushes.</i>

02:17.637 --> 02:19.773
<i>They call it a crush</i>
<i>because chances are</i>

02:19.806 --> 02:22.776
<i>if you open your mouth,</i>
<i>you're gonna get crushed.</i>

02:22.809 --> 02:25.612
<i>They could have called it,</i>
<i>"She don't like you, stupid,"</i>

02:25.645 --> 02:27.681
<i>but "crush" is just quicker.</i>

02:29.282 --> 02:30.717
<i>That's Tangee Brown.</i>

02:32.552 --> 02:33.687
Hi.

02:33.720 --> 02:35.655
<i>All she ever</i>
<i>said to me was "hi."</i>

02:35.689 --> 02:40.994
<i>That's all I needed. After</i>
<i>that, she became my bus crush.</i>

02:41.027 --> 02:42.529
<i>I call it a bus crush</i>

02:42.562 --> 02:44.431
<i>because this one</i>
<i>happened on a bus.</i>

02:44.464 --> 02:48.668
<i>One time</i>
<i>I had an elevator crush.</i>

02:48.702 --> 02:51.871
<i>I almost lost my head</i>
<i>trying to follow her around.</i>

02:51.905 --> 02:53.640
<i>There was my window crush.</i>

02:53.673 --> 02:55.809
[SCREAMING]
[SCREAMING]

02:55.842 --> 02:58.812
<i>The laws about that were a lot</i>
<i>more relaxed at the time.</i>

02:58.845 --> 03:01.715
<i>There was only</i>
<i>one problem with my bus crush:</i>

03:01.748 --> 03:03.350
<i>she had a boyfriend.</i>

03:03.383 --> 03:05.585
Why I gotta be stupid?
<i>You</i>lost your hat.

03:05.618 --> 03:07.921
I was trying to keep you
from getting on the wrong bus.

03:07.954 --> 03:10.290
Oh, so I'm dumb now?
Yeah, Tangee.

03:10.323 --> 03:11.858
And you're getting on my nerves.

03:11.891 --> 03:13.460
[BELL DINGS]

03:13.493 --> 03:15.962
Clyde, you still got my books.
Here.

03:15.995 --> 03:18.598
You need to read them. Maybe
they'll teach you how to act.

03:18.631 --> 03:20.600
<i>This must be</i>
<i>how the drummer felt</i>

03:20.633 --> 03:23.269
<i>watching Ike and Tina fight.</i>

03:23.303 --> 03:25.305
Thank you.
You want to sit down?

03:25.338 --> 03:26.539
No, that's okay.

03:26.573 --> 03:28.975
Oh, no, it's all right.
I like to stand.

03:29.009 --> 03:30.643
Thanks.

03:30.677 --> 03:32.012
<i>At that moment,</i>

03:32.045 --> 03:34.681
<i>somebody could have sold me</i>
<i>a lifetime bus pass.</i>

03:36.416 --> 03:37.984
[MOUTHS]
<i>I love you.</i>

03:38.018 --> 03:40.520
CHRIS ROCK:
<i>My mother loved</i>
<i>Valentine's Day,</i>

03:40.553 --> 03:42.856
<i>and why not?</i>
<i>I learned early on,</i>

03:42.889 --> 03:45.392
<i>Valentine's Day</i>
<i>is not a day for couples,</i>

03:45.425 --> 03:46.993
<i>it's a day for women.</i>

03:47.027 --> 03:50.830
<i>If a woman shows up at a man's</i>
<i>door empty-handed, big deal.</i>

03:50.864 --> 03:53.667
<i>But if a man shows up</i>
<i>empty-handed,</i>

03:53.700 --> 03:55.835
<i>he may as well</i>
<i>not have shown up at all.</i>

03:55.869 --> 03:57.437
WOMAN: Die, you pig!
Aah!

03:57.470 --> 03:59.372
<i>He won't forget next year.</i>

03:59.406 --> 04:01.441
ROCHELLE: Hello?
GIRL:<i>Can I talk to Drew?</i>

04:01.474 --> 04:03.376
Drew can't come
to the phone right now.

04:03.410 --> 04:05.345
We're having dinner.
<i>I'm his valentine.</i>

04:05.378 --> 04:07.313
His who?
<i>His valentine.</i>

04:07.347 --> 04:10.684
<i>His only valentine.</i>
Okay, bye.

04:10.717 --> 04:12.919
Drew, you need
to tell these fast little girls

04:12.952 --> 04:15.455
to stop calling
all hours of the day and night.

04:15.488 --> 04:17.057
I told them already.
Tell them again.

04:17.090 --> 04:21.494
They're all calling, "Well,
tell him his valentine called."

04:21.528 --> 04:23.029
I don't have time for that.

04:23.063 --> 04:25.498
Relax. Boy can't help it
if he's popular.

04:25.532 --> 04:28.401
Chris, how many valentine cards
did you get so far?

04:28.435 --> 04:30.704
None.
How come girls don't like you?

04:30.737 --> 04:32.372
None of your business,
that's why.

04:32.405 --> 04:35.642
Don't get mad at me.
Hey, hey, hey.

04:35.675 --> 04:38.912
Mama, can you help me make
a Valentine's Day card?

04:38.945 --> 04:40.413
JULIUS:
A homemade card.

04:40.447 --> 04:42.649
That's my little girl,
saving that money.

04:42.682 --> 04:45.719
Sure, baby. Who's it for?
My boyfriend.

04:45.752 --> 04:47.787
[***]

04:47.821 --> 04:50.390
Your what friend?
Well, the girl can't help it

04:50.423 --> 04:51.891
if she's popular.

04:54.728 --> 04:57.831
Where'd you get a boyfriend?
At school.

04:57.864 --> 05:00.900
Ma, do you have a place
where I can put all my cards?

05:00.934 --> 05:02.369
How many you giving out, boy?

05:02.402 --> 05:04.104
Well, I'm not really
giving them out.

05:04.137 --> 05:05.839
Girls just keep
giving them to me.

05:05.872 --> 05:07.540
JULIUS:
My man.

05:07.574 --> 05:10.143
Are girls supposed to give boys
Valentine's Day cards?

05:10.176 --> 05:11.578
They're giving them to him.

05:11.611 --> 05:13.880
What's that
got to do to with me?

05:13.913 --> 05:16.716
How long
have you had a boyfriend?

05:16.750 --> 05:17.851
Just for a week.

05:17.884 --> 05:19.919
Rochelle?
Julius.

05:19.953 --> 05:23.156
I wish somebody would give me
a Valentine's Day card that says

05:23.189 --> 05:24.891
something besides "I hate you."

05:24.924 --> 05:27.093
Well, if you want,
you can have one of mine.

05:27.127 --> 05:30.430
<i>And I thought getting</i>
<i>his hand-me-downs was bad.</i>

05:30.463 --> 05:31.965
Mm, no, thank you.

05:31.998 --> 05:35.001
Who gave you a card
that said "I hate you"?

05:35.035 --> 05:37.437
Oh, I don't know.

05:37.470 --> 05:38.938
It's just a stupid joke.

05:38.972 --> 05:41.141
<i>Even though</i>
<i>I didn't like Caruso,</i>

05:41.174 --> 05:45.612
<i>I didn't think he deserved</i>
<i>to be cursed out by my mother.</i>

05:45.645 --> 05:47.714
<i>Even though</i>
<i>my father wasn't romantic,</i>

05:47.747 --> 05:49.716
<i>he wasn't stupid, either.</i>

05:49.749 --> 05:51.985
<i>He had a box full of</i>
<i>greeting cards in the house.</i>

05:52.018 --> 05:56.022
<i>He could give my mother</i>
<i>a card for any occasion.</i>

05:56.056 --> 05:57.991
<i>Happy Anniversary.</i>

05:58.024 --> 06:01.161
Aw, you shouldn't have.

06:01.194 --> 06:04.030
<i>Happy Flag Day.</i>

06:04.064 --> 06:06.966
Oh, you shouldn't have.

06:07.000 --> 06:09.436
<i>Happy Chanukah.</i>

06:09.469 --> 06:12.605
Oh, you shouldn't have.

06:12.639 --> 06:14.808
<i>He used to keep</i>
<i>candy under the bed too,</i>

06:14.841 --> 06:17.410
<i>but the mice kept eating it.</i>

06:18.645 --> 06:20.613
[ROCHELLE CLEARS THROAT]

06:23.650 --> 06:25.752
Hey, babe.
Hey, baby.

06:25.785 --> 06:26.986
This is for you.

06:28.755 --> 06:31.558
Baby, it's not even
Valentine's Day yet.

06:31.591 --> 06:36.129
I know, but every day
is special with you.

06:36.162 --> 06:39.032
Oh, Julius, you didn't have to.

06:39.065 --> 06:40.967
But since you did...

06:43.670 --> 06:45.939
You see all this right here?
You see that?

06:45.972 --> 06:48.174
That's why Tonya don't need
to be running around

06:48.208 --> 06:50.043
talking about
she got a boyfriend.

06:50.076 --> 06:52.045
Julius, she's 10 years old.

06:52.078 --> 06:55.015
He's just a boy in her class.
It's no big deal.

06:55.048 --> 06:56.616
Rochelle, do you watch the news?

06:56.649 --> 06:58.151
Girls are having babies at 10.

06:58.184 --> 06:59.886
<i>And grandbabies at 20.</i>

06:59.919 --> 07:02.255
Drew is the one
you need to be worried about.

07:02.288 --> 07:05.692
What for?
So a few girls like him.

07:05.725 --> 07:08.028
There's nothing wrong with that.
He's 11.

07:08.061 --> 07:09.796
He's only
one year older than Tonya.

07:09.829 --> 07:12.265
Pssht.
What is the difference?

07:12.298 --> 07:13.933
She is a girl.

07:13.967 --> 07:18.505
Baby, you cannot protect
Tonya from everything.

07:18.538 --> 07:21.074
You wanna bet? Watch me.

07:21.107 --> 07:23.810
I'll protect her
from everything. Everything.

07:23.843 --> 07:26.680
<i>It was clear that my father</i>
<i>already had a plan.</i>

07:26.713 --> 07:29.616
Daddy, this is Ronald.
My fiancé.

07:29.649 --> 07:31.551
Nice to meet you, sir.

07:33.253 --> 07:35.221
[GROANS]

07:35.255 --> 07:38.224
Mama! Daddy shot
my fiancé again.

07:38.258 --> 07:42.262
<i>Hey, say what you want, but</i>
<i>that's effective birth control.</i>

07:42.295 --> 07:43.863
[SCHOOL BELL RINGS]

07:43.897 --> 07:46.766
Hey, why do girls like guys
that are mean to them?

07:46.800 --> 07:48.268
Nice guys finish last.

07:48.301 --> 07:51.004
Maybe the mean guys beat
the crap out of the nice guys

07:51.037 --> 07:53.807
so when the girls show up,
no one else is around.

07:53.840 --> 07:55.175
Did you say anything
to her?

07:55.208 --> 07:58.111
I picked up her books
and I offered her a seat.

07:58.144 --> 07:59.746
Oh, man, this is major.

07:59.779 --> 08:01.114
What's her name?
Tangee.

08:01.147 --> 08:02.982
Greg, this is for you.

08:03.016 --> 08:04.851
Oh, yeah.

08:04.884 --> 08:07.087
Please don't open it
until I leave.

08:07.120 --> 08:08.688
Promise?
Okay.

08:08.722 --> 08:11.658
[***]

08:11.691 --> 08:13.193
Valentine's Day card?

08:13.226 --> 08:14.961
It says "Be mine."

08:14.994 --> 08:16.629
Okay.

08:17.630 --> 08:19.699
Yeah.

08:19.733 --> 08:23.603
Man, "Be my valentine,"
that's so cool.

08:23.636 --> 08:25.772
Hey, look, you got one too.

08:28.041 --> 08:31.578
"Roses are red,
violets are blue...

08:31.611 --> 08:35.148
cupid hates your guts,
and I do too."

08:35.181 --> 08:38.351
Well, at least this time
he wrote a poem.

08:38.385 --> 08:41.121
[LAUGHS]
[CHUCKLES]

08:43.189 --> 08:45.892
<i>I never knew when</i>
<i>I'd see Tangee on the bus,</i>

08:45.925 --> 08:48.628
<i>so I was always excited</i>
<i>when I saw her get on.</i>

08:48.661 --> 08:50.163
TANGEE: Let me go!
No.

08:50.196 --> 08:52.632
<i>Unfortunately, she was</i>
<i>always excited too.</i>

08:52.665 --> 08:56.736
<i>Not "happy" excited, more</i>
<i>like "hold me back" excited.</i>

08:56.770 --> 08:59.706
Look what you did to my jacket.
It's all stretched out.

08:59.739 --> 09:01.141
If you got on like I said,
it wouldn't have happened.

09:01.174 --> 09:03.777
You ain't my daddy.
I don't have to do what you say.

09:03.810 --> 09:05.612
Push me again
and see what happens.

09:05.645 --> 09:08.148
Hey. Leave her alone.

09:08.181 --> 09:10.250
What?
You heard him.

09:10.283 --> 09:12.018
What you gonna do now?

09:12.052 --> 09:14.754
<i>Hey, I don't need any help</i>
<i>getting my ass whupped.</i>

09:14.788 --> 09:16.723
<i>That's the one thing</i>
<i>I'm good at.</i>

09:16.756 --> 09:20.126
<i>* Everybody hates Chris </i>

09:29.202 --> 09:32.238
Mind your business.
<i>I couldn't back down now.</i>

09:32.272 --> 09:35.208
<i>I was scared if I moved</i>
<i>I might pee myself.</i>

09:35.241 --> 09:36.743
No.

09:36.776 --> 09:39.646
Get the hell off my bus, boy.

09:39.679 --> 09:42.182
Okay.
Not you. You.

09:42.215 --> 09:44.351
Come on, let's go.
Why I got to get off?

09:44.384 --> 09:46.353
He started it.
Quit lying.

09:46.386 --> 09:47.987
He ain't start nothing.

09:48.021 --> 09:50.690
Why don't you quit lying?
I said, get off.

09:50.724 --> 09:52.892
Now move.

09:56.996 --> 09:59.032
[BUS DOORS OPEN]

09:59.065 --> 10:00.934
You want to sit down?

10:00.967 --> 10:02.769
Sure.

10:04.804 --> 10:07.240
Why'd you do that?
I don't know.

10:07.273 --> 10:08.908
I wasn't thinking, I guess.

10:08.942 --> 10:10.944
My father said you're not
supposed to hit a girl.

10:10.977 --> 10:13.713
You know your father?
Yeah.

10:15.181 --> 10:17.784
Nobody's ever looked out for me
like that before.

10:17.817 --> 10:19.352
What's your name?
Chris.

10:19.386 --> 10:21.788
[***]

10:27.127 --> 10:29.162
I'm Tangee.

10:29.195 --> 10:30.797
Here.

10:30.830 --> 10:32.365
A Valentine's Day card?

10:32.399 --> 10:36.970
Yeah. I was gonna give it
to Clyde, but he makes me sick.

10:37.003 --> 10:38.938
Thanks.
<i>This was great,</i>

10:38.972 --> 10:40.440
<i>my first Valentine's.</i>

10:40.473 --> 10:43.243
<i>So what if it was meant</i>
<i>for a future wife beater?</i>

10:43.276 --> 10:44.711
<i>He ain't beat me.</i>

10:44.744 --> 10:46.880
[DOORBELL BUZZES]

10:46.913 --> 10:49.449
Hi. Is Drew home?

10:49.482 --> 10:51.184
Do you realize
it's 8:30 at night?

10:51.217 --> 10:52.986
Drew is in bed.

10:53.019 --> 10:54.821
He is 11.

10:54.854 --> 10:57.724
E-L-E-V-E-N, 11.

10:57.757 --> 10:59.059
I--
Go home.

10:59.092 --> 11:00.860
If I see you
around my child again,

11:00.894 --> 11:03.396
I'm calling the cops. Got that?
Yeah, I--

11:03.430 --> 11:07.033
Okay, I know all of that.
I know, girl, I know.

11:07.067 --> 11:08.435
Beat it.

11:09.502 --> 11:12.806
Ooh, these are my favorites.

11:12.839 --> 11:14.874
Mm! Mm-mm-mm.

11:14.908 --> 11:17.944
All right, bye, Dad.
See you later, son.

11:17.977 --> 11:20.880
Daddy, you haven't walked us
to school in a long time.

11:20.914 --> 11:23.516
I know. It's been a while.

11:23.550 --> 11:25.885
Aren't you supposed
to be sleeping?

11:25.919 --> 11:28.755
Yeah. I can get my rest later.

11:28.788 --> 11:31.391
Mama said you don't like
walking us to school.

11:31.424 --> 11:33.126
That's not true.

11:33.159 --> 11:34.894
You want a dollar?
Yeah.

11:34.928 --> 11:38.064
All right. There you go.

11:39.332 --> 11:41.267
Hey, since I'm here,

11:41.301 --> 11:44.437
why don't you show me which one
of these kids is your boyfriend?

11:44.471 --> 11:47.207
Oh, um...there he is.

11:47.240 --> 11:48.875
James!

11:50.477 --> 11:53.246
So that's him, huh?
Yeah.

11:53.279 --> 11:54.848
All right.

11:56.082 --> 11:59.185
Bye, Daddy.
All right, bye, baby.

12:04.057 --> 12:05.792
Can I talk to you for a minute?

12:05.825 --> 12:06.893
[CHILDREN CLAMORING]

12:06.926 --> 12:08.194
Who, me?
Yeah, you.

12:08.228 --> 12:10.397
Get over here.
What's your name?

12:10.430 --> 12:12.832
My name is "Don't worry
about what my name is."

12:12.866 --> 12:15.168
What, you think you're some
kind of ladies' man?

12:15.201 --> 12:18.071
I don't know any ladies.
They're not even ladies to you?

12:18.104 --> 12:20.306
No. Uh, I don't know...

12:20.340 --> 12:23.043
Who are you?
Don't worry about who I am.

12:23.076 --> 12:25.178
Worry about
who you're giving them cards to.

12:25.211 --> 12:28.081
I want my mama.
Oh, so you a mama's boy?

12:28.114 --> 12:30.817
Yes.
Well, listen up, mama's boy.

12:30.850 --> 12:33.586
You stay away from
my daughter, you hear me?

12:33.620 --> 12:35.088
Huh?

12:35.121 --> 12:35.955
[CRYING]

12:35.989 --> 12:37.357
Hey, man, stop that.

12:37.390 --> 12:38.892
Hey, stop that.

12:38.925 --> 12:40.226
MAN:
Hey, stay away from that boy!

12:40.260 --> 12:43.530
Get out of here!
I was just talking to him.

12:43.563 --> 12:46.132
MAN:
Hey, you, I'm talking to you!

12:46.166 --> 12:48.968
<i>While my father was getting rid</i>
<i>of Tonya's valentine,</i>

12:49.002 --> 12:51.971
<i>I wish he'd been around</i>
<i>to get rid of mine.</i>

12:52.005 --> 12:54.040
[***]

12:54.074 --> 12:57.210
"Roses are red,
violets are blue...

12:58.511 --> 13:01.448
Please go back to Africa
and take your mother with you.

13:01.481 --> 13:02.849
[LAUGHING]

13:02.882 --> 13:05.151
Happy Valentine's Day."
BOY: Moron.

13:05.185 --> 13:08.955
<i>Another card like this,</i>
<i>and I might just go to Africa.</i>

13:11.024 --> 13:12.359
What's wrong with you?

13:12.392 --> 13:14.427
I'm trying not to bump
into Joy again.

13:14.461 --> 13:16.062
The school's only but so big.

13:16.096 --> 13:18.164
You're bound to run
into her sometimes.

13:18.198 --> 13:20.266
I just don't know
what my next move is.

13:20.300 --> 13:22.502
Well, did you get her a card?
No.

13:22.535 --> 13:24.537
Then that's your next move.

13:24.571 --> 13:27.407
You can come with me.
I was gonna go get one anyway.

13:27.440 --> 13:28.975
For who?

13:29.009 --> 13:31.311
The girl on the bus.
She gave me one yesterday.

13:31.344 --> 13:32.879
And you didn't tell me?

13:32.912 --> 13:34.381
I go to bed early,
but you can call

13:34.414 --> 13:36.583
and wake me up when something
this important happens.

13:36.616 --> 13:38.351
Well, I wanted
to tell you in person.

13:38.385 --> 13:40.320
I broke up a fight between
her and her boyfriend.

13:40.353 --> 13:43.523
You broke up a fight?
Yeah, and she gave me this card.

13:43.556 --> 13:45.025
Dude, this is huge.

13:45.058 --> 13:46.893
Is it? I-I don't know.

13:46.926 --> 13:49.029
It... It's just a card.

13:49.062 --> 13:51.297
A card is,
"I'm yours for the taking."

13:51.331 --> 13:54.200
How in there do you have to be
before you get it?

13:54.234 --> 13:56.169
Why is it
that when it comes to me,

13:56.202 --> 13:58.171
you know so much about girls,

13:58.204 --> 14:00.440
but you freak out
when one gives you a card?

14:00.473 --> 14:04.310
I guess it's kind of like not
being able to cut your own hair.

14:04.344 --> 14:06.413
<i>Before you ever</i>
<i>buy a girl a gift,</i>

14:06.446 --> 14:10.050
<i>the first thing you've got to</i>
<i>do is buy her the perfect card.</i>

14:10.083 --> 14:11.351
Nah, that's too much.

14:11.384 --> 14:14.954
You haven't even
kissed her yet. Have you?

14:14.988 --> 14:19.459
Um...how about this one?

14:19.492 --> 14:20.927
"You know the deal.

14:20.960 --> 14:22.462
I want you to be my valentine."

14:22.495 --> 14:26.433
That's cool, but it's more
for a friend than a girl.

14:26.466 --> 14:29.135
Whoa, cool.

14:29.169 --> 14:32.238
"Relatively speaking,
would you be my valentine?"

14:32.272 --> 14:36.509
This is perfect.
For Tangee? No, thanks.

14:36.543 --> 14:37.677
No, for Joy.

14:37.711 --> 14:39.612
<i>Greg never fought being a nerd.</i>

14:39.646 --> 14:42.682
<i>I always wondered</i>
<i>how that worked out for him.</i>

14:42.716 --> 14:45.418
[***]

14:45.452 --> 14:46.619
[HORN HONKING]

14:46.653 --> 14:48.388
Come on, honey!

14:50.990 --> 14:52.726
Greg, when did you get
this car?

14:52.759 --> 14:55.261
Well, the Bentley's
in the shop.

15:01.434 --> 15:03.003
I kind of like this one.

15:04.671 --> 15:08.108
Dude, this card is $2.50.

15:08.141 --> 15:10.377
Hey, you've gotta pay
to play, right?

15:15.448 --> 15:18.251
Quick, give me my card.

15:18.284 --> 15:19.219
Here.

15:19.252 --> 15:21.054
Here. This is for you.

15:21.087 --> 15:23.189
Thank you.
GREG: No, no, no, no.

15:23.223 --> 15:25.392
Read it when you get home.
Okay.

15:28.094 --> 15:30.630
Man, that was close.

15:30.663 --> 15:32.432
What's this?

15:32.465 --> 15:34.234
Oh, ha, ha, very funny.

15:37.470 --> 15:39.406
Chris!

15:39.439 --> 15:40.473
How could you?

15:40.507 --> 15:43.443
When I found out how Caruso
had been teasing you,

15:43.476 --> 15:46.546
I thought you'd appreciate
a real valentine from someone.

15:46.579 --> 15:49.349
Obviously, I was wrong.
<i>Nowadays, you wish</i>

15:49.382 --> 15:51.718
<i>all the teacher</i>
<i>gave your kids were cards.</i>

15:51.751 --> 15:55.422
I didn't know it was yours.

15:55.455 --> 15:58.491
<i>While I couldn't have been</i>
<i>less popular, back at home,</i>

15:58.525 --> 16:01.027
<i>Drew couldn't have been</i>
<i>more popular.</i>

16:01.061 --> 16:03.163
[PHONE RINGS]

16:04.297 --> 16:06.433
Hello?
GIRL:<i>Is my valentine home yet?</i>

16:06.466 --> 16:09.035
No, Drew is
still outside playing.

16:09.069 --> 16:11.171
Stop calling here!

16:11.204 --> 16:12.572
What's wrong, what's wrong?

16:12.605 --> 16:13.707
All these girls calling.

16:13.740 --> 16:15.442
It's getting on my nerves.

16:15.475 --> 16:17.277
I already have
enough to deal with.

16:17.310 --> 16:20.180
Can you believe some maniac
threatened the kids?

16:20.213 --> 16:22.482
I've gotta go pick them up
from school today.

16:22.515 --> 16:24.684
Well, at least Drew's there
to protect Tonya.

16:24.718 --> 16:27.687
Now, what are we gonna do
about Drew and these girls?

16:27.721 --> 16:30.090
Huh? What?

16:30.123 --> 16:31.458
Julius, every five minutes,

16:31.491 --> 16:33.626
some girl is calling
or knocking at the door.

16:33.660 --> 16:37.163
Drew is way too young
to get this much attention.

16:37.197 --> 16:40.333
Rochelle, it's nothing, okay?

16:40.367 --> 16:42.335
Drew's only 11 years old.

16:42.369 --> 16:44.070
He don't care
about those girls.

16:44.104 --> 16:46.539
Boys are becoming fathers
even at age 12.

16:46.573 --> 16:49.442
CHRIS ROCK:
<i>And great-grandfathers at 43.</i>

16:49.476 --> 16:51.144
Baby, relax.

16:51.177 --> 16:52.212
Don't worry about it.

16:52.245 --> 16:53.713
You don't worry about it,

16:53.747 --> 16:56.716
'cause I ain't about to let
nobody call me Grandmama.

16:56.750 --> 16:58.485
<i>With my mother on the job,</i>

16:58.518 --> 17:01.421
<i>I didn't get a girl</i>
<i>till I was 33.</i>

17:01.454 --> 17:05.792
<i>Meanwhile, Drew had more girls</i>
<i>than an Usher after-party.</i>

17:07.394 --> 17:09.229
Happy Valentine's Day, Drew.

17:09.262 --> 17:12.432
Oh, thank you, Miss Johnson.
Uh-huh.

17:12.465 --> 17:15.435
<i>As bad as my Valentine's Day</i>
<i>had been going, I knew</i>

17:15.468 --> 17:18.772
<i>I could count on my bus crush</i>
<i>to make it all right.</i>

17:18.805 --> 17:21.474
Hey, Chris, I saved you a seat.

17:24.377 --> 17:26.112
Thanks.

17:28.248 --> 17:30.450
Can I ask you something?
What?

17:30.483 --> 17:33.653
How come you go with a guy
that you always fight with?

17:33.687 --> 17:37.857
I'm not going with him anymore.
He's stupid.

17:37.891 --> 17:39.359
<i>That's all I needed to hear.</i>

17:39.392 --> 17:41.161
Hey, I got you something.

17:41.194 --> 17:43.830
Really? That's so sweet.

17:43.863 --> 17:46.132
What else?

17:46.166 --> 17:47.467
What else, what?

17:47.500 --> 17:50.270
Where's the gift?
I only got you a card.

17:50.303 --> 17:52.605
That's it?
It's Valentine's Day,

17:52.639 --> 17:56.276
and all you got me was
this cheap-ass card?

17:56.309 --> 17:58.445
I-I just met you.
So?

17:58.478 --> 18:00.413
Where's the flowers?
Where's the candy?

18:00.447 --> 18:02.382
I thought I meant
something to you.

18:02.415 --> 18:03.850
I thought we had a connection.

18:03.883 --> 18:06.553
You know, I could have stayed
with Clyde's sorry ass

18:06.586 --> 18:08.555
if this is how you
were gonna treat me.

18:08.588 --> 18:10.490
Can you please quiet down?
You don't tell me to be quiet.

18:10.523 --> 18:13.493
Why don't you be quiet?
Better yet, shut up!

18:13.526 --> 18:16.296
Gonna tell me to be quiet.
You ain't my daddy!

18:16.329 --> 18:17.897
<i>Getting cursed out on a bus</i>

18:17.931 --> 18:21.267
<i>is not really how I expected</i>
<i>to end my Valentine's Day,</i>

18:21.301 --> 18:22.702
<i>but it did prove my point.</i>

18:22.736 --> 18:25.338
<i>If you have a crush,</i>
<i>you get crushed.</i>

18:25.372 --> 18:27.440
This is a piece of paper!
I don't need this!

18:27.474 --> 18:30.410
<i>Where was the bus driver</i>
<i>with a bat when you needed him?</i>

18:30.443 --> 18:32.278
I kissed your
little funky cheek,

18:32.312 --> 18:33.780
but I could have
stayed with Clyde.

18:33.813 --> 18:37.317
Here, take back your stupid
card. I do not need this.

18:40.420 --> 18:43.723
Drew, you gotta return
these cards to Miss Johnson.

18:43.757 --> 18:45.859
A 30-year-old married woman

18:45.892 --> 18:48.828
giving cards
to my 11-year-old son.

18:48.862 --> 18:51.231
What about the candy?

18:51.264 --> 18:54.501
I think sending
the cards back makes the point.

18:57.370 --> 18:59.372
<i>Giving the card to Tangee</i>
<i>didn't work out,</i>

18:59.406 --> 19:01.608
<i>but I knew my mother</i>
<i>would appreciate one.</i>

19:01.641 --> 19:03.510
Thank you, sweetie.

19:03.543 --> 19:06.279
You didn't have to give me
a card.

19:06.312 --> 19:08.648
I already know that you love me.

19:08.682 --> 19:10.383
[CHUCKLES]

19:11.651 --> 19:13.653
Who the hell is Joy?

19:15.955 --> 19:18.792
Joy, are you dating a black guy?

19:18.825 --> 19:20.593
<i>She did, five years later.</i>

19:20.627 --> 19:24.397
<i>* Everybody hates Chris </i>

19:27.267 --> 19:30.637
[***]

19:30.670 --> 19:33.373
<i>* Aw, make it funky now </i>
